CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1958, pg. B4 reads: :" "Honeybunnies" At Sunday School - These "honeybunnies" were enjoying their Easter Sunday school lesson at the Brushton Methodist Church when The Courier photographer dropped in to pay a visit. Not being at all camera-shy, they stopped long enough to give with their best smiles.  With them are Mrs. J.D.Barkley, left, and Mrs. Cato Wimbish, right, Sunday school teachers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Sunday school teachers Mrs. J. D.Barkley, left, and Cato Wimbish, right, posed with seven boys and ten girls around table in Brushton Methodist Church on Easter Sunday
